[1] Omissions in 2008 importation data
Date: Tue 14 Aug 2009
From: Kathleen Harriman <Kathleen.Harriman@cdph.ca.gov>


I would like to make some corrections to the 2008 measles importation
data reported in the ProMED-mail post archived as "Measles -
chronology of importations 20090414.1419." (Data for other years is
also incomplete).

California reported 12 cases of measles in 2008 that were related to
a traveler infected in Switzerland. However, the cases in Arizona
were not related to the California cases and were the result of a
separate importation from Switzerland. There were no additional cases
related to the infected infant who traveled from California to Hawaii.

In 2008, there were 3 other imported measles cases reported in
California; one infected in India, one in Italy, and one in Viet Nam.

In 2009, there have been 3 measles cases reported in California to
date, a case infected in England and 2 contacts of this case.

--
Kathleen Harriman, PhD, MPH, RN
Chief, Vaccine Preventable Disease Epidemiology Section
Immunization Branch
California Department of Public Health
850 Marina Bay Parkway
Richmond, CA 94804
<kathleen.harriman@cdph.ca.gov>

